### Create a New Person [POST]

This action creates a new person.
The `name` parameter is required; the `birthday` parameter is optional.
The format of the `birthday` will be auto-interpreted, so you may pass `"12 May 2015"`, `"May 12, 2015"`, "`2015-05-12`", etc.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name": "Erica Sample",
            "birthdate": "12 August 2017"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "birthdate": "2017-08-12",
                "created_at": "2019-11-26T00:32:27.955Z",
                "id": 22,
                "name": "Erica Sample",
                "updated_at": "2019-11-26T00:32:27.955Z"
            }
            
## Actions On Specific People [/people/{person_id}]
            
### Edit a Person [PUT]

This action edits an existing person.
Pass the `name` or `birthdate` you wish to edit in the payload.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "birthdate": "15 August 2017"
        }
    
+ Response 204 (application/json)

### Delete a Person [DELETE]

This action deletes an existing person.

+ Response 204